  "prompt": "Where can I get audiobooks for free in English?",
  "response": "There are several platforms where you can access free audiobooks in English. Here are some options:\n\n1. **LibriVox**: This site offers free audiobooks read by volunteers. It\u2019s a good place to find classic literature and older works that are in the public domain.\n\n2. **Project Gutenberg**: While primarily known for free eBooks, Project Gutenberg also offers a collection of free audiobooks, both human-read and computer-generated.\n\n3. **Loyal Books**: Formerly known as Books Should Be Free, this site offers free audiobooks from the public domain and provides them in various formats.\n\n4. **Open Culture**: This educational website has a section that links to free audiobooks from various sources, including classic literature and contemporary works.\n\n5. **Lit2Go**: This collection from Florida's Educational Technology Clearinghouse offers free downloadable audiobooks and poems that can also be used for K-12 educational purposes.\n\n6. **Internet Archive**: This digital library offers free access to thousands of audiobooks in addition to its vast collection of texts, music, and more.\n\n7. **Spotify**: Though primarily a music streaming service, Spotify offers a selection of audiobooks, especially public domain classics, available for free listening.\n\n8. **YouTube**: Many users upload and share audiobooks, including complete readings of classics and popular books. Searching for a specific title plus \u201caudiobook\u201d can yield results.\n\n9. **Bibliomania**: This site features free literature including audiobooks, alongside study guides and analyses.\n\nRemember to check the licensing and availability on these platforms, as some books might only be partially available or have specific conditions regarding their use.",
